spec: mp3466
version: ">=3.9"
backend: python_module(multiprocessing)

docs: https://docs.python.org/3/library/multiprocessing.html

provenance:
  derived_from:
    - "https://docs.python.org/3/library/multiprocessing.html"
    - "https://docs.python.org/3/library/multiprocessing.managers.html"
    - "Test vectors verified with Python 3.14.4 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-13"
  not_derived_from:
    - "CPython source code"
    - "any proprietary source"
  notes:
    - "Wave 678 (mp3466): __iter__, __next__, __len__ dict-presence (iter(x), next(x), len(x)) for multiprocessing types."
    - "Theme: __iter__/__next__/__len__ dict-presence (iter(x), next(x), len(x))."
    - "All values False — these types do not implement the iterator or sizing protocol in their own __dict__."
    - "All values verified with Python 3.14.4 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-13."
    - "Classes covered: multiprocessing.Process, pool.Pool, pool.AsyncResult, pool.MapResult, managers.SyncManager, managers.BaseListProxy, managers._BaseDictProxy, managers._BaseSetProxy."
    - "Key finding (__iter__): all 8 multiprocessing classes return false for __iter__. iter(x) calls __iter__ when defined in the class's own __dict__. multiprocessing.Process: a subprocess lifecycle manager with no __iter__ in its own __dict__. pool.Pool/AsyncResult/MapResult: work-dispatch and result-handle types with no custom __iter__ in their own __dict__. managers.SyncManager: server process manager with no __iter__ in its __dict__. managers.BaseListProxy: proxies list — BaseListProxy does NOT define __iter__ in its own __dict__ despite proxying list iteration at runtime via the proxy dispatch mechanism. managers._BaseDictProxy: proxies dict; __iter__ is absent from its own __dict__ (key iteration is relayed via proxy dispatch, not a locally defined dunder). managers._BaseSetProxy: proxies set; __iter__ is not defined in its own __dict__ (set iteration is relayed via proxy dispatch)."
    - "Key finding (__next__): all 8 multiprocessing classes return false for __next__. next(x) delegates to __next__ when defined in the class's own __dict__. multiprocessing types do not define __next__ in their own __dict__. The proxy types (_BaseSetProxy, _BaseDictProxy, BaseListProxy) relay iterator advancement to the managed server process via IPC but do not define __next__ in their own __dict__. multiprocessing.Process: __next__ is absent from Process.__dict__. pool.Pool/AsyncResult/MapResult/SyncManager: no __next__ defined in their own __dict__."
    - "Key finding (__len__): all 8 multiprocessing classes return false for __len__. len(x) delegates to __len__ when defined in the class's own __dict__. multiprocessing types define no sizing protocol in their own __dict__. managers._BaseDictProxy key note: _BaseDictProxy proxies dict and supports len() via IPC, but __len__ is not defined in its own __dict__ at the Python class level. managers.BaseListProxy: proxies list length at runtime via proxy dispatch; __len__ is not defined in BaseListProxy.__dict__. managers._BaseSetProxy: proxies set length via proxy dispatch; __len__ is absent from its own __dict__. multiprocessing.Process/pool.Pool/AsyncResult/MapResult/SyncManager: process-management types with no __len__ in their own __dict__."
    - "All 24 values in this wave are false. multiprocessing is a process-based concurrency library; its types interact exclusively through explicit method calls, subprocess lifecycle management, and IPC — not through iterator or sizing protocol overrides in any class __dict__."
    - "Proxy type clarification: managers.BaseListProxy, _BaseDictProxy, and _BaseSetProxy proxy their respective collection types to a managed server process via IPC. At runtime, iteration and sizing are relayed through the proxy dispatch mechanism — not through __iter__, __next__, __len__ defined directly in their own Python-level __dict__."
    - "Cross-wave summary for mp subjects:"
    - "  Wave 658 (mp3166): __add__/__sub__/__mul__ — BaseListProxy __add__=true, __mul__=true; others false."
    - "  Wave 659 (mp3181): __truediv__/__floordiv__/__mod__ — all false for all 8."
    - "  Wave 660 (mp3196): __pow__/__lshift__/__rshift__ — all false for all 8."
    - "  Wave 661 (mp3211): __and__/__or__/__xor__ — all false for all 8."
    - "  Wave 662 (mp3226): __radd__/__rsub__/__rmul__ — all false for all 8."
    - "  Wave 663 (mp3241): __rtruediv__/__rfloordiv__/__rmod__ — all false for all 8."
    - "  Wave 664 (mp3256): __rpow__/__rlshift__/__rrshift__ — all false for all 8."
    - "  Wave 665 (mp3271): __rand__/__ror__/__rxor__ — all false for all 8."
    - "  Wave 666 (mp3286): __iadd__/__isub__/__imul__ — all false for all 8."
    - "  Wave 667 (mp3301): __itruediv__/__ifloordiv__/__imod__ — all false for all 8."
    - "  Wave 668 (mp3316): __ipow__/__ilshift__/__irshift__ — all false for all 8."
    - "  Wave 669 (mp3331): __iand__/__ior__/__ixor__ — all false for all 8."
    - "  Wave 670 (mp3346): __neg__/__pos__/__abs__ — all false for all 8."
    - "  Wave 671 (mp3361): __invert__/__floor__/__ceil__ — all false for all 8."
    - "  Wave 672 (mp3376): __trunc__/__round__/__index__ — all false for all 8."
    - "  Wave 673 (mp3391): __int__/__float__/__complex__ — all false for all 8."
    - "  Wave 674 (mp3406): __bool__/__str__/__repr__ — all false for all 8."
    - "  Wave 675 (mp3421): __hash__/__eq__/__lt__ — all false for all 8."
    - "  Wave 676 (mp3436): __le__/__gt__/__ge__ — all false for all 8."
    - "  Wave 677 (mp3451): __getitem__/__setitem__/__delitem__ — all false for all 8."
    - "  Wave 678 (mp3466): __iter__/__next__/__len__ — all false for all 8."
  created_at: "2026-04-13"

error_model: python_exceptions

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# __iter__ dict-presence — operator.contains(Cls.__dict__, '__iter__')
#
# All 8 multiprocessing classes return false for __iter__.
# iter(x) calls __iter__ when defined in the class's own __dict__.
# multiprocessing.Process: a subprocess lifecycle manager; iteration
#   is not part of the Process API. __iter__ is absent from Process.__dict__.
# pool.Pool/AsyncResult/MapResult: work-dispatch and result-handle types
#   with no custom __iter__ defined in their own __dict__.
# managers.SyncManager: server process manager with no __iter__ in its
#   __dict__.
# managers.BaseListProxy: proxies list iteration at runtime via IPC proxy
#   dispatch, but does NOT define __iter__ in its own Python-level __dict__.
# managers._BaseDictProxy: proxies dict key iteration at runtime via IPC; no
#   __iter__ is defined in its own __dict__.
# managers._BaseSetProxy: proxies set iteration via proxy dispatch; __iter__
#   is not defined in its own __dict__.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

table mp3466.iter:
  description: "multiprocessing types __iter__ dict-presence checks; wave 678"
  kind: python_call_eq
  version: ">=3.9"
  error_model: python_exceptions
  category: dict_contains
  id_prefix: mp3466

  columns: [id, function, args, expected]
  rows:
    - ["mp3466001", operator.contains, [multiprocessing.Process.__dict__,                 "__iter__"], false]
    - ["mp3466002", operator.contains, [multiprocessing.pool.Pool.__dict__,               "__iter__"], false]
    - ["mp3466003", operator.contains, [multiprocessing.pool.AsyncResult.__dict__,        "__iter__"], false]
    - ["mp3466004", operator.contains, [multiprocessing.pool.MapResult.__dict__,          "__iter__"], false]
    - ["mp3466005", operator.contains, [multiprocessing.managers.SyncManager.__dict__,    "__iter__"], false]
    - ["mp3466006", operator.contains, [multiprocessing.managers.BaseListProxy.__dict__,  "__iter__"], false]
    - ["mp3466007", operator.contains, [multiprocessing.managers._BaseDictProxy.__dict__, "__iter__"], false]
    - ["mp3466008", operator.contains, [multiprocessing.managers._BaseSetProxy.__dict__,  "__iter__"], false]

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# __next__ dict-presence — operator.contains(Cls.__dict__, '__next__')
#
# All 8 multiprocessing classes return false for __next__.
# next(x) delegates to __next__ when defined in the class's own __dict__.
# multiprocessing types do not define __next__ in their own __dict__; iterator
#   advancement falls back to proxy dispatch or raises TypeError at runtime.
# managers._BaseDictProxy: relays iterator advancement to the managed server
#   process via IPC proxy dispatch, but does not define __next__ in its own __dict__.
# managers.BaseListProxy: relays iterator advancement via proxy dispatch; no
#   __next__ in its own __dict__.
# managers._BaseSetProxy: relays set iterator advancement via proxy dispatch;
#   __next__ is absent from its own __dict__.
# multiprocessing.Process: __next__ is absent from Process.__dict__.
# pool.Pool/AsyncResult/MapResult/SyncManager: no __next__ customization
#   in their own __dict__.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

